result.execSummary:
The defendant Jordan O Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Movable Property <=$2500, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Cases 15CF381 and 15CF314 called together at 3:35pm [mo]
Defendant Jordan O Johnson in court with Attorney Jeffrey Jacob De La Rosa.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

--service of Information admitted, reading waived

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest " entered on Case 15CF381  and Count #1 of Case 15CF314; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

On Motion of the State, the Court reads in and dismisses: Count #2 of Case 15CF314

Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
--ADA Teuber submits Victim Impact Statement

On Case 15CF381:
The Court sentences Defendant to:
--serve 6 months in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges; to be served consecutive to any sentence in being

--Mr. Johnson is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence and the alternate sentence, if served, with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--to pay restitution in the amount of $130.50 to Phillip Parmley (joint and several)--Restitution is to be converted to civil judgment
--pay costs of $268 plus 250 DNA surcharge= $518
--provide DNA Sample upon demand

On Case 15CF314: 
--serve 90  days in Jefferson County Jail, with Huber privileges; to be served consecutive to 15CF381 and any other sentence in being
--0 days credit for time already served given
--Mr. Johnson is required to report for commencement and service of jail sentence and the alternate sentence, if served, with absolute sobriety and without controlled substances in system; non-compliance will result in loss of Huber privileges without further process.
--pay costs of $243 plus $200 DNA surcharge= $443, 
--provide DNA Sample upon demand

 The total court costs for both cases, $961.00 is to be paid in $35 per month installments commencing on 12/31/16 and on the last day of each month thereafter until paid in full; 
As to Case 15CF381: non-payment shall result in a 11  day jail term with Huber privileges, consecutive
As to Case 15CF314: non-payment shall result in a 9  day jail term with Huber privileges, consecutive

The Court grants Mr. Johnson the ability to serve the jail sentences in another county, so long as it is without electronic monitoring and served as it would be in Jefferson County.
